HEADWORD: Pluralist
<hw>Plu"ral*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A clerk or
clergyman who holds more than one ecclesiastical benefice.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of the parochial clergy, a large proportion were
<qex>pluralists</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plurality</ent>⟦br⟧
